docs.lead_paragraph: A major manufacturer of birth-control devices announced yesterday the recall of 86,000 diaphragms manufactured under the brand name Koro-Flex during a four-month period in 1976. Some of the devices are defective.

headline.main: Consumer Notes; Birth Control Device Recalled by the Manufacturer

docs.abstract: FTC probes milk price-setting policies in 11 states to see if price regulation has anticompetitive effect on milk prices (S)
